>>> #addTag
### `addTag`
<<<

>>> #addTag-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.addTag(tag)
```

Adds a specified `tag` to the entity.
Note that this is **not** an entity **type** tag, but entity tag which can be applied to using a command:
```
/tag <entity> add <name>
```

**Parameters**

- `[js]tag`: The entity tag to add.

**Return value**
None (`[js]undefined`). 
<<<

| <#addTag>             |
| <#addTag-description> |
