>>> #is
### `is`
<<<

>>> #is-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.is(otherEntity)
```

**Parameters**
- `[js]otherEntity`: An {Entity}.

**Return value**
`true` is `[js]entity` and `[js]otherEntity` refer to the same exact object.
Ender Dragons are composed of {EnderDragonPart} mobs, so `is` will also return `[js]true` if the {EnderDragonPart} is a part of the exact {EnderDragon} provided.
