>>> #get-uuid-set-uuid
### `getUuid`, `setUuid`
<<<

>>> #get-uuid-set-uuid-description
>>> info
This method has its name *slightly* changed from vanilla: `setUUID`, `getUUID`.
These have been lowercased to make the beans created from those lowercase as well.
<<<

**Syntax**
```js
entity.getUuid()

entity.setUuid(uuid)

entity.uuid // bean
```

Gets or sets the entity's UUID. Corresponds to `UUID` NBT tag on the entity.

**Setter parameter**
- `[js]uuid`: A {UUID} to set. It may be a string representing a UUID, for example `[js]'9839ba5f-87fa-4718-aeab-f2b6d74a2385'`.

**Getter return value**
A {UUID} of the entity.
<<<

| <#get-uuid-set-uuid>             |
| <#get-uuid-set-uuid-description> |

