>>> #lookat
### `lookAt`
<<<

>>> #lookat-description
```js
entity.lookAt(anchor, targetPos)
```

Makes the entity look at the point in 3D space respecting the provided `[js]anchor`. Usually, the anchor should be `[js]'eyes'` for realistic "looking at" logic.

**Parameters**
- `[js]anchor`: A {EntityAnchorArgument$Anchor} enumeration, that specifies the initial point. String representations of possible values are:
  - `[js]'eyes'` - Position of the eyes of the entity will be the initial point.
  - `[js]'feet'` - Position of the entity (its feet) will be the initial point.
- `[js]targetPos`: A {Vec3} representing a point in 3D space at which the entity will look at. It may be a JS array of 3 numbers, for example `[js]\[70.5, -60, 108.5\]`.

**Return value**
None (`[js]undefined`).
<<<

| <#lookat>             |
| <#lookat-description> |

