>>> #getPose-setPose
### `getPose`, `setPose`
<<<

>>> #getPose-setPose-description
**Syntax**
```js
entity.getPose()

entity.setPose(pose)

entity.pose // bean
```

Gets or sets the entity's pose.

**Setter parameter**
- `[js]pose`: The new entity's {Pose}. String representations of possible values are: `[js]'standing'`, `[js]'fall_flying'`, `[js]'sleeping'`, `[js]'swimming'`, `[js]'spin_attack'`, `[js]'crouching'`, `[js]'long_jumping'`, `[js]'dying'`, `[js]'croaking'`, `[js]'using_tongue'`, `[js]'sitting'`, `[js]'roaring'`, `[js]'sniffing'`, `[js]'emerging'`, `[js]'digging'`, `[js]'sliding'`, `[js]'shooting'`, `[js]'inhaling'`.

**Getter return value**
The entity's current {Pose}. Can be loosely compared to by its string value.
<<<

| <#getPose-setPose>             |
| <#getPose-setPose-description> |

