<<<

>>> #isDiscrete-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.isDiscrete()
entity.discrete // read-only bean
```

Checks if the entity is considered discrete / sneaky.

In vanilla, discrete entities hide their name tags behind blocks. Foxes won't avoid (run away from) discrete players.

By default, all entities that [press the "Sneak" key](#isshiftkeydown-setshiftkeydown) are considered to be discrete.

**Return value**
`[js]true` if the entity is considered discrete, `[js]false` if it isn't.
<<<

| <#isDiscrete> |
| <#isDiscrete-description> |
