>>> #isVisuallySwimming
### `isVisuallySwimming`
<<<

>>> #isVisuallySwimming-description

**Syntax**
```js
entity.isVisuallySwimming()
entity.visuallySwimming // read-only bean
```

Checks if the entity is visually swimming.

By default, entities are visually swimming if they are in the `SWIMMING` pose, but entities may override this behavior. For example, Drowned are visually swimming if they are [actually swimming](#isswimming-setswimming).

**Return value**
`[js]true` if the entity is visually swimming, `[js]false` if it isn't.
<<<

| <#isVisuallySwimming> |
| <#isVisuallySwimming-description> |
