>>> #can-trample
### `canTrample`
<<<

>>> #can-trample-description
**Syntax**
```js
entity.canTrample(blockState, pos, fallDistance)
```

Checks, whether the `[js]entity` can trample a block with `[js]blockState` at a given `[js]pos` after falling for `[js]fallDistance` blocks.

Note that the check involves some randomness, as the fall distance required to trample the block can vary.

**Parameters**
- `[js]blockState`: The {BlockState} to trample.
- `[js]pos`: The {BlockPos} of a block. It may be a 3-element JS array representing the block position, like `[js]\[64, 50, -20\]`.
- `[js]fallDistance`: The distance from which the entity fell.

**Return value**
`[js]true` if the entity can trample that block, `[js]false` if it can't.

<<<

| <#can-trample>             |
| <#can-trample-description> |

