>>> #tell
### `tell`
<<<

>>> #tell-description
**Syntax**
```js
entity.tell(component)
```

Sends a system message to the entity into their chat.

**Parameters**
- `[js]component`: A text {Component} which holds the chat message. See [[/ref/wrappers/TextWrapper|`Text`]] for more information about possible formatting options. It can be also a string, which will be implicitly wrapped into a text component.

**Return value**
None (`[js]undefined`).

**Example**
The following example sends a message in chat greeting the player that joins the server, with their nickname colored green:
```js
PlayerEvents.loggedIn(event => {
	event.player.tell(Text.ofString('Welcome back, ').append(Text.green(event.player.username)).append('!'))
})
```

Simple string messages are also supported:
```js
PlayerEvents.loggedIn(event => {
	event.player.tell(`Welcome back, ${event.player.username}!`)
})
```
<<<

| <#tell>             |
| <#tell-description> |

